# Building an LSTM model

model = Sequential()
model.add(Input(shape=(None,49)))
model.add(LSTM(activation='relu', units=128, return_sequences=True, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
model.add(Dropout(0.2))
model.add(LSTM(activation='relu', units=64, return_sequences=True, kernel_initializer='he_normal'))
model.add(Dropout(0.1))
model.add(Dense(units = 49, activation='relu', kernel_initializer = tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal()))

# Creating first 8 patches for above 100 test images and predicting the bottom patch

fig, ax = plt.subplots(10,10, figsize=(12,12))
for i in range(10):
  for j in range(10):
    # Creating first 8 patches for each image
    ind = class_index[i,j]
    patch = test_features[ind][0:8,:]
    img = patch.reshape(1,8,49)

    counter = 7
    # Predicting rest 7 patches
    for k in range(7):
      pred = model.predict(img)
      img = np.concatenate((img, pred[:,counter,:].reshape(1,1,49)), axis=1)
      counter += 1

    rec_img = zeros((1,49))
    rec_img1 = np.concatenate((test_features[ind][0:8,:], img[0,8:,:], rec_img))
    rec_img1 = rec_img1.reshape(16,7,7)
    final_img = zeros((28,28))
    m = 0
    for t in range(0,28,7):
      for v in range(0,28,7):
        final_img[t:t+7,v:v+7] = rec_img1[m]
        m = m+1
    ax[i][j].imshow(final_img)

# Building the encoder

class Sampling(layers.Layer):

    def call(self, inputs):
        z_mean, z_log_var = inputs
        batch = tf.shape(z_mean)[0]
        dim = tf.shape(z_mean)[1]
        epsilon = tf.keras.backend.random_normal(shape=(batch, dim))
        return z_mean + tf.exp(0.5 * z_log_var) * epsilon

# Function for variational autoencoder

class VAE(keras.Model):
    def __init__(self, encoder, decoder, **kwargs):
        super(VAE, self).__init__(**kwargs)
        self.encoder = encoder
        self.decoder = decoder
        self.total_loss_tracker = keras.metrics.Mean(name="total_loss")
        self.reconstruction_loss_tracker = keras.metrics.Mean(
            name="reconstruction_loss"
        )
        self.kl_loss_tracker = keras.metrics.Mean(name="kl_loss")

    @property
    def metrics(self):
        return [
            self.total_loss_tracker,
            self.reconstruction_loss_tracker,
            self.kl_loss_tracker,
        ]

    def train_step(self, data):
        with tf.GradientTape() as tape:
            z_mean, z_log_var, z = self.encoder(data)
            reconstruction = self.decoder(z)
            reconstruction_loss = tf.reduce_mean(
                tf.reduce_sum(
                    keras.losses.binary_crossentropy(data, reconstruction), axis=(1, 2)
                )
            )
            kl_loss = -0.5 * (1 + z_log_var - tf.square(z_mean) - tf.exp(z_log_var))
            kl_loss = tf.reduce_mean(tf.reduce_sum(kl_loss, axis=1))
            total_loss = reconstruction_loss + kl_loss
        grads = tape.gradient(total_loss, self.trainable_weights)
        self.optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(grads, self.trainable_weights))
        self.total_loss_tracker.update_state(total_loss)
        self.reconstruction_loss_tracker.update_state(reconstruction_loss)
        self.kl_loss_tracker.update_state(kl_loss)
        return {
            "loss": self.total_loss_tracker.result(),
            "reconstruction_loss": self.reconstruction_loss_tracker.result(),
            "kl_loss": self.kl_loss_tracker.result(),
        }

# Building the discriminator model

def discriminator():
  model = Sequential()
  dis_img = Input(shape=(784,))
  dis_label = Input(shape=(10,))
  dis_input = Concatenate(axis=1)([dis_img, dis_label])

  model.add(Dense(units=400, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.3))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(units=200, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(units=100, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
  model.add(Dropout(0.1))
  model.add(Dense(units=1, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer='GlorotNormal'))

  dis_pred = model(dis_input)
  dis_model = Model([dis_img, dis_label], dis_pred, name = 'discriminator')
  
  return dis_model
 
gan_dis = discriminator()
opt = Adam(lr=0.0002, beta_1=0.5)
gan_dis.compile(loss = 'binary_crossentropy', optimizer = opt, metrics = ['binary_accuracy'])
print(gan_dis.summary())

# Building the generator model

def generator():
  model = Sequential()
  gen_img = Input(shape=(100,))
  gen_label = Input(shape=(10,))
  gen_input = Concatenate(axis=1)([gen_img, gen_label])

  model.add(Dense(units=200, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
  model.add(BatchNormalization(momentum=0.8))
  model.add(Dense(units=400, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
  model.add(BatchNormalization(momentum=0.8))
  model.add(Dense(units=784, activation='tanh', kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))

  gen_pred = model(gen_input)

  gen_model = Model([gen_img, gen_label], gen_pred, name = 'generator')
  
  return gen_model

gan_gen = generator()
print(gan_gen.summary())

# Training the generator and discriminator

def cganTraining(epochs, n_batch):
  real_labels = ones((n_batch, 1))
  fake_labels = zeros((n_batch, 1))
  real_batch_acc = []
  fake_batch_acc = []
  for i in range(epochs):    
    for j in range(0,len(x_train),n_batch):
      gan_dis.trainable = True
      
      # Generating real samples
      x_real, labels_real = x_train[j:j+n_batch,:], y_train[j:j+n_batch,:]
      y_real = real_labels[:len(labels_real),:]
      d_loss_real, d_acc_real = gan_dis.train_on_batch([x_real, labels_real], y_real)

      # Generating fake samples
      x_fake = np.random.normal(0,1,size = (n_batch, latent_dim))
      labels_fake = np.eye(num_classes)[np.random.choice(num_classes, n_batch,replace=True)]
      y_fake =  fake_labels[:len(labels_fake),:]
      gen_pred = gan_gen.predict([x_fake,labels_fake])
      d_loss_fake, d_acc_fake = gan_dis.train_on_batch([gen_pred, labels_fake], y_fake)

      # Training the generator
      gan_dis.trainable = False
      x_gan = np.random.normal(0,1,size = (n_batch, latent_dim))
      labels_gan = np.eye(num_classes)[np.random.choice(num_classes, n_batch,replace=True)]
      g_loss = cgan_model.train_on_batch([x_gan,labels_gan], real_labels)

    real_batch_acc.append(d_acc_real)
    fake_batch_acc.append(d_acc_fake)
  
  return (real_batch_acc,fake_batch_acc)

history = cganTraining(100, 128)

# Building the discriminator model

def discriminator():
  model = Sequential()
  dis_img = Input(shape=(784,))
  dis_label = Input(shape=(10,))
  dis_input = Concatenate(axis=1)([dis_img, dis_label])

  model.add(Dense(units=400, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.3))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(units=200, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(Dense(units=100, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
  model.add(Dropout(0.1))
  model.add(Dense(units=1, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer='GlorotNormal'))

  dis_pred = model(dis_input)
  dis_model = Model([dis_img, dis_label], dis_pred, name = 'discriminator')
  
  return dis_model
 
gan_dis = discriminator()
opt = Adam(lr=0.0002, beta_1=0.5)
gan_dis.compile(loss = 'binary_crossentropy', optimizer = opt, metrics = ['binary_accuracy'])
print(gan_dis.summary())

# Building the generator model

def generator():
  model = Sequential()
  gen_img = Input(shape=(100,))
  gen_label = Input(shape=(10,))
  gen_input = Concatenate(axis=1)([gen_img, gen_label])

  model.add(Dense(units=200, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
  model.add(BatchNormalization(momentum=0.8))
  model.add(Dense(units=400, kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))
  model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.2))
  model.add(BatchNormalization(momentum=0.8))
  model.add(Dense(units=784, activation='tanh', kernel_initializer='HeNormal'))

  gen_pred = model(gen_input)

  gen_model = Model([gen_img, gen_label], gen_pred, name = 'generator')
  
  return gen_model

gan_gen = generator()
print(gan_gen.summary())

def gans_training(epochs, n_batch, lmb):
  real_labels = ones((n_batch, 1))
  fake_labels = zeros((n_batch, 1))
  real_batch_acc = []
  fake_batch_acc = []
  for i in range(epochs):    
    for j in range(0,len(x_train)-n_batch,n_batch):
      gan_dis.trainable = True
      
      # Generating real samples
      x_real, labels_real = x_train[j:j+n_batch,:], y_train[j:j+n_batch,:]
      y_real = real_labels[:len(labels_real),:]
      d_loss_real, d_acc_real = gan_dis.train_on_batch([x_real, labels_real], y_real)
      
      # Generating fake samples
      x_fake1 = x_real.reshape([-1,28,28]) 
      x_fake = x_fake1[:,9:19,9:19].reshape(-1,100)
      labels_fake = np.eye(num_classes)[np.random.choice(num_classes, n_batch,replace=True)]
      y_fake =  fake_labels[:len(labels_fake),:]
      gen_pred = gan_gen.predict([x_fake,labels_fake])
      d_loss_fake, d_acc_fake = gan_dis.train_on_batch([gen_pred, labels_fake], y_fake)

      # Training the generator
      gan_dis.trainable = False
      x_gan = np.random.normal(0,1,size = (n_batch, latent_dim))
      labels_gan = np.eye(num_classes)[np.random.choice(num_classes, n_batch,replace=True)]
      gen_pred1 = gen_pred.reshape([-1,28,28]) 
      gen_pred2 = gen_pred1[:,9:19,9:19].reshape(-1,100)
      g_loss = cgan_model.train_on_batch([x_gan,labels_gan], real_labels) + lmb * np.mean(np.square(gen_pred2 - x_gan))

    real_batch_acc.append(d_acc_real)
    fake_batch_acc.append(d_acc_fake)
  
  return (real_batch_acc,fake_batch_acc)
